import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['x', 'y'])
    plt.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['lumosity'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['lumosity'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['lumosity'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Lumosity')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['saturation'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['saturation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['saturation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Saturation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of saturation?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    color_counts = data['color'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(color_counts.index, color_counts.values, color=color_counts.index)
    ax.set_xlabel('Color')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of color?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(data['key'].value_counts().index, data['key'].value_counts().values, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of key?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Key')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
